Specifically, they’re trying to resurrect the Equal Rights Amendment, the radical feminist constitutional amendment the rest of us had long thought a dead issue.
Women are perfectly capable of flexing political power: They make up the majority of voters in nearly every election.
Sex discrimination is already forbidden under both federal and state laws, as well as by the Equal Protection Clause of the 14th Amendment.
While many still think about the ERA as a relic of history, the amendment will be a live issue going into 2020.
Which is why opponents must prepare to argue on the substance: Men and women are already equal under American law, but they aren’t the same.